            {
              "id": "lp2009_s2_text_prompt_2",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "The term Aztec refers to the empire of the Mexicas. In Nahuatl, the native language of the Mexicas, it means “someone who comes from Aztlan”, a place commonly believed to be situated in northern Mexico or the southwest U.S. It is applied to all the people linked by trade, custom, religion and language."
            },
            {
              "id": "lp2009_s2_text_prompt_3",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "The society traditionally was divided into two social classes: the Macehualli (people) or peasantry and the Pilli or nobility. In the later days of the empire, the concept of Macehualli had changed: only 20% of the population were dedicated to agriculture and food production. The other 80% of society were not only warriors, but also skilled artisans and aggressive traders. Eventually, most of the Macehuallis were dedicated to arts and crafts. Their works were an important source of income for the city."
            },
            {
              "id": "lp2009_s2_text_prompt_4",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "The Mexica, one of the Aztec groups, were one of the first people in the world to have mandatory education for nearly all children. There were two types of schools: the telpochcalli, for practical and military studies, and the calmecac, for advanced learning in writing, astronomy, statesmanship, and theology. Until the age of 14, the education of children was in the hands of their parents, but supervised by the authorities. Periodically they attended their local temples to test their progress."
            },
            {
              "id": "lp2009_s2_text_prompt_5",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "Adapted from Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia."
            },
            {
              "id": "lp2009_s2_text_prompt_6",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "* Compulsory/obligatory"
            }
          ]
        },
